      • getExternalApplicationVersionIndication

        public java.lang.String getExternalApplicationVersionIndication()
        If your connector only supports specific versions of the external application (for example, 2.0+ or 1.1.0-1.2.0), return this information here as a string.
        By default, returns null (no specific version constraint on the external application).
        Returns:
        application's version

      • getConnectorVersion

        public abstract java.lang.String getConnectorVersion()
        Returns:
        the version of this connector, as a String. Will be ignored if returning null or an empty String, but it is strongly suggested to set this to a relevant version number and increment it with every new connector release.

      • getTargetApplicationIcon

        public java.lang.String getTargetApplicationIcon()
        Get image icon of target application. By default, return a white question mark in a blue circle.
        We strongly advise to replace this with the logo of the external application.
        Returns:
        HTTP URL or Data URI of the image

        public abstract java.util.List<FunctionIntegration> getIntegrations()
        Get implementations of Integration points
        Returns:

        See Also:
        TimeSheetIntegration, WorkPlanIntegration

      • getBuiltInDefaultInstance

        public IntegrationConnectorInstance getBuiltInDefaultInstance()
        Get the build-in instance of this connector. If defined, this connector instance will be created by default in the PPM "Integration/Hybrid" configuration page, and PPM admins will not be able to create one manually.
        By default, no default connector instance is defined (returns null).
        Returns:
        the default connector instance, if any.
        See Also:
        "PPM Sub Projects connector"
